summary: An Ordinance appropriating money from the General Fund to pay for a deficiency in the cost of the improvement of Thirty-seventh Avenue, in the City of Seattle, from Fifty (50) feet north of the north line of East Spring Street to the north lien of Rosedale Addition to the City of Seattle, by constructing concrete sidewalks thereon, as provided for in Ordinance No. 12912, creating Local Improvement District No. 1145.
